<tr id="L309"><td><a href="#L309">309</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kang is injured as well, and joins Koloth</td></tr>

<tr id="L310"><td><a href="#L310">310</a></td><td>KOLOTH:  I will not die before you, you thunderous bulk.</td></tr>

<tr id="L311"><td><a href="#L311">311</a></td><td>KOR:  The story of your courage will never die. I will sing the story. The children of all Klingons will know of this day.</td></tr>

<tr id="L312"><td><a href="#L312">312</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Koloth dies</td></tr>

<tr id="L313"><td><a href="#L313">313</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kang deals with the guard that the Albino is cowering behind.</td></tr>

<tr id="L314"><td><a href="#L314">314</a></td><td>ALBINO:  You'll die far quicker than your son did, Kang.</td></tr>

<tr id="L315"><td><a href="#L315">315</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Finally the two old enemies go head to head. Dax finishes off the last guard as Kang breaks his bat'leth against a railing. The Albino stabs him in the stomach.</td></tr>

<tr id="L316"><td><a href="#L316">316</a></td><td>ALBINO:  No vengeance today, Kang.</td></tr>

<tr id="L317"><td><a href="#L317">317</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Dax knocks the weapon out of the Albino's hand</td></tr>

<tr id="L318"><td><a href="#L318">318</a></td><td>ALBINO:  And who are you, girl?</td></tr>

<tr id="L319"><td><a href="#L319">319</a></td><td>DAX:  You knew me as Curzon Dax.</td></tr>

<tr id="L320"><td><a href="#L320">320</a></td><td>ALBINO:  The Trill. Of course. You're far too young and lovely to sport such a deadly weapon. All right, then.</td></tr>

<tr id="L321"><td><a href="#L321">321</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The Albino puts his neck in the curve of the blade</td></tr>

<tr id="L322"><td><a href="#L322">322</a></td><td>ALBINO:  Use it, if that's what you came to do. Kill me in cold blood. Run me through the belly and cut out my heart. Isn't that what your blood oath promised? Or have you lost your appetite, my dear.</td></tr>

<tr id="L323"><td><a href="#L323">323</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kang stabs the laughing Albino in the back</td></tr>

<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>KANG:  Thank you for saving the death blow for me. You have honoured me one last time, godfather to my son.</td></tr>

<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kor staggers amongst the corpses</td></tr>

<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>KANG:  Where is Koloth?</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>KOR:  He is dead.</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>KANG:  I was right, Dax. It is a good day to die.</td></tr>

<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: And does so.</td></tr>

<tr id="L330"><td><a href="#L330">330</a></td><td>DAX:  It's never a good day to lose a friend.</td></tr>

<tr id="L331"><td><a href="#L331">331</a></td><td>KOR:  Ki-naH-naH, lo-maytool. Ki-nah-nah, lo-maytaH.</td></tr>

